subsection.def:
aircraft (飛機) means
                any machine which can derive support in the atmosphere from reactions of the
                air;

authorized officer (獲授權人員) means a public officer authorized by the
                Commissioner under section 4;
                (Amended L.N. 294 of 1982)

Commissioner (關長) means the Commissioner of Customs and Excise and any Deputy or
                Assistant Commissioner of Customs and Excise;
                (Added L.N. 294 of 1982. Amended 65 of 2000 s. 3)

electronic record (電子紀錄) has the meaning given to that term in section 2(1) of
                the Electronic Transactions Ordinance (Cap. 553);
                (Added 24 of 2002 s. 3)

export (出口) means to
                take or cause to be taken out of Hong Kong any article other than an article in
                transit;

import (進口) means to
                bring or cause to be brought into Hong Kong any article other than an article in
                transit;

information system (資訊系統) has the meaning given to that term in
                    section 2(1) of the Electronic Transactions Ordinance (Cap. 553);
                (Added 24 of 2002 s. 3)

sale (售賣) and
                    purchase (購買) include a sale and
                purchase by barter;

security device (保安裝置) means a device issued to a person to be used for authenticating
                that person as the sender of information using a recognized electronic service;
                (Added 24 of 2002 s. 3)

value-added service provider (增值服務提供者) means a person approved under section
                    18(2) to transmit, on behalf of another person, any specified information
                using the specified system; (Added 30 of 2025 s. 76)
